text.section:
To facilitate the Office completing its duties under subsection (a) of this section, a contractor shall:
allow the Office to inspect any relevant matter, including records and the job site;
allow the Office to interview subcontractors and employees of the contractor;
if performing a construction contract, ensure that subcontractors:
are paid any undisputed amount to which the subcontractor is entitled as provided under § 15-226 of the State Finance and Procurement Article; and
comply with Commission regulations;
include in the agreement with the certified minority business enterprise subcontractor a requirement that the subcontractor submit a monthly report to the Commission that:
identifies the prime contract; and
lists payments received from the contractor in the previous month and invoices sent to the contractor that have not been paid; and
submit a monthly report to the Commission that lists:
unpaid invoices that are more than 30 days old received from certified minority business enterprise subcontractors; and
the reason payments have not been made.
